CRITICAL SAFETY WARNING — PLEASE READ BEFORE USE

This skill gives an AI agent (Claude or any skill-aware assistant) the
ability to execute arbitrary JavaScript against your local OmniFocus
database with full read/write privileges via macOS osascript. There is
NO sandboxing and NO per-call confirmation — the only safeguards are
instructions in the skill telling the agent to confirm destructive
actions before performing them, which is enforcement by convention,
not by mechanism.

Potential consequences of misuse include but are not limited to:
- Permanent deletion of tasks, projects, folders, and tags
- Silent or bulk modification or corruption of OmniFocus data
- Loss of historical completion records, notes, and tags
- No undo for destructive operations

Risks specific to AI-driven use:
- An agent may misinterpret a request and run a destructive query
- A prompt-injection payload reaching the agent (via task notes,
  pasted content, or external context) could direct it to delete or
  modify data
- A buggy or hallucinated query may produce unintended writes

